social networking law 2008 risks and opportunities stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff calendar social networking law 2008 risks and opportunities go back details march 5 2008 from 5 00 pm 8 00 pm reception 5 30 6 30 pm law lounge panel 6 30 8 30 pm room 290 stanford law school social networking sites have changed the way we work play and interact with one another they also raise a host of legal issues join us for a lively discussion of cutting edge legal issues surrounding social networks the panel of industry experts will address both the law and best practices in this field including the ugc principles and best practices to address copyright and other ip infringement issues the protection of children in social networks open apis vs closed systems business opportunities and legal risks different models for privacy and anonymity in social networks special terms of use issues spamming phishing and other forms of abuse panelists mike angus general counsel fox interactive media susan infantino product counsel google inc chris kelly chief privacy officer facebook jay monahan vice president and general counsel vuze inc moderator ian ballon greenberg traurig llp this event is free and open to the public register at http lst stanford edu social_networking website related media social networking law 2008 risks and opportunities streaming video 150k social networking law 2008 risks and opportunities streaming audio 56k contact tech law stanford edu 650 723 5905 related stanford program in law science & technology cloudy 50 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
